---

# Project Overview

This assignment demonstrates the implementation of a complete CI/CD pipeline for a Node.js To-Do application using GitHub Actions, Docker, DockerHub, and Render.com.

The pipeline automates:
1. Building a Docker image
2. Pushing the Docker image to DockerHub
3. Deploying the application automatically on Render.com

---

# Technologies Used

| Tool/Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| GitHub | Source code hosting |
| GitHub Actions | CI/CD automation |
| Docker | Containerization |
| DockerHub | Docker image registry |
| Render.com | Cloud deployment |
| Node.js | Backend runtime |
| npm | Package management |

